column20:
Instead of adding boolean * wepgone to more things, change them to send an object pointer pointer so that the called function is able to nullify the caller's copy of the object pointer.
Minimalistic example:
hmon(&weapon);
if(!weapon) {
    // weapon was destroyed in hmon()
}

